{"type":"message","id":"035cfdbe","parentId":"d2febab1","timestamp":"2026-03-30T06:33:52.691Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_a744fbf8c99f4119bd0511e5","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Notion database ID 33299624-0a66-818e-92d0-dabaca1c1ec8\",\n  \"provider\": \"duckduckgo\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 943,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"duckduckgo\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d8e53fef33be650a\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nRetrieve a database - Notion Docs\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d8e53fef33be650a\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://developers.notion.com/reference/retrieve-a-database\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d6a2a57ea81aac70\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nRetrieves a database object â information that describes the structure and columns of a database â for a provided database ID . The response adheres to any limits to an integration's capabilities. To fetch database rows rather than columns, use the Query a database endpoint. To find a database ID , navigate to the database URL in your Notion workspace. The ID is the string of characters in ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d6a2a57ea81aac70\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"developers.notion.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"834c40464a90006d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nHow to find your Notion Database ID - easlo.co\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"834c40464a90006d\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.easlo.co/blog/how-to-find-notion-database-id\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a24807d15f77d869\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nA database ID is the unique identifier of a database you have created in Notion . When setting up Notion integrations in automation tools like Zapier, Make, or Apple Shortcuts, you may need to input your database ID .\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a24807d15f77d869\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.easlo.co\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"566b538380db65da\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nWhere to find Database Id for my database in Notion?\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"566b538380db65da\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/67728038/where-to-find-database-id-for-my-database-in-notion\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a5ff1127959ef95d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nI have been using notion to track my habits and my finances. Now I want to get the data from the database using the Notion API. But the notion API requires Database ID and I can't seem to find it.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a5ff1127959ef95d\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"stackoverflow.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"94afa203d1243eb5\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nHow to Find Database ID in Notion - Notion Tour\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"94afa203d1243eb5\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://notiontour.com/blog/database-id-in-notion\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"78992e55fb30fa56\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nWhen building apps or services on top of notion , you will need to have the database ID to get access to the database and use the database accordingly. In this article, we will see how you can find your database id from your Notion workspace.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"78992e55fb30fa56\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"notiontour.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c089609ca31c63a3\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nNotion Database ID - Create with Notion\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c089609ca31c63a3\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://createwithnotion.com/notion-database-id/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"62255bf4f6a6b763\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe Database ID is the part of the URL that comes after the workspace name and the word \\\"d\\\". Alternatively, users can use the Notion API to programmatically retrieve the Database ID . Once users have the Database ID , they can use it to perform a variety of actions, such as querying the database , adding new entries, or updating existing entries.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"62255bf4f6a6b763\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"createwithnotion.com\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"Notion database ID 33299624-0a66-818e-92d0-dabaca1c1ec8","provider":"duckduckgo","count":5,"tookMs":943,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"duckduckgo","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d8e53fef33be650a\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nRetrieve a database - Notion Docs\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d8e53fef33be650a\">>>","url":"https://developers.notion.com/reference/retrieve-a-database","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d6a2a57ea81aac70\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nRetrieves a database object â information that describes the structure and columns of a database â for a provided database ID . The response adheres to any limits to an integration's capabilities. To fetch database rows rather than columns, use the Query a database endpoint. To find a database ID , navigate to the database URL in your Notion workspace. The ID is the string of characters in ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d6a2a57ea81aac70\">>>","siteName":"developers.notion.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"834c40464a90006d\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nHow to find your Notion Database ID - easlo.co\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTEN