{"type":"message","id":"49aa5c24","parentId":"c3cf1505","timestamp":"2026-03-30T06:40:52.294Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking \"what even is yt dlp\" with low reasoning effort. I need to explain yt-dlp simply and conversationally. Since we're in Telegram format now (after removing strict double line breaks), I should use clear, friendly language with possible emojis or bold for emphasis, but follow the new formatting guidelines from SOUL.md/IDENTITY.md/AGENTS.md: use emojis, **bold**, *italics*, visual markers, double line breaks between paragraphs, horizontal rules for sections, concise sentences.\n\nI should explain yt-dlp as a tool for downloading YouTube videos and extracting subtitles/transcripts, mention it's a fork of youtube-dl, commonly used for getting transcripts for the YouTube Research skill.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"âĸ y"},{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me craft a response.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"t-dlp is a **command-line tool** that downloads videos and extracts subtitles/transcripts from YouTube and many other sites\n\nâĸ Think of it as a \"YouTube video + caption grabber\" that works in your terminal\n\nâĸ It's a **fork** of the older youtube-dl project, but actively maintained with more features and fixes\n\nâĸ For our YouTube Research skill:\n  âĸ Search and video details work without it (uses YouTube API directly)\n  âĸ **Transcript extraction requires yt-dlp** â that's how we get the actual text from videos\n\nâĸ Installation is simple:\n  âĸ `pip install yt-dlp` (recommended â works on any OS with Python)\n  âĸ Or `sudo apt install yt-dlp` on Linux\n\nâĸ Once installed, our skill can pull full transcripts, timestamped segments, and word counts from any video with captions available\n\nâĸ Want me to install it for you so we can try transcript features? Or would you prefer to search for some videos first without transcripts?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":54270,"output":383,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54653,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774852838660,"responseId":"chatcmpl-9e51586cd2868768"}}
