{"type":"message","id":"76d3380e","parentId":"c1dd5e5a","timestamp":"2026-03-30T07:19:06.375Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to respond. Explain that yt-dlp does not transcribe audio, only extracts existing captions. No local transcriber in script. Offer to add","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"âĸ The current script **"},{"type":"thinking","thinking":" if desired.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"only extracts existing captions/subtitles** from YouTube (via ytâdlp or the YouTube timedtext API). It does **not** download the audio and run a local speechâtoâtext transcriber.\n\nâĸ Adding a local transcriber (e.g., using Whisper, Vosk, or another speechâtoâtext model) is certainly possible, but it would require:\n  1. Downloading the video/audio with ytâdlp\n  2. Running a transcription model on the audio file\n  3. Handling larger dependencies, compute time, and potential offline model sizes\n\nâĸ If youâd like, I can sketch out how to extend the skill with an optional transcription mode (e.g., `--transcribe-audio` that uses a lightweight model like Whisper Tiny). Let me know if you want to explore that, or if youâre happy with the current captionâonly approach for now.\n\nâĸ Otherwise, the skill is ready for search, video details, and extracting existing transcripts. Shall we try a video known to have captions, or move on to another task?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":67974,"output":275,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68249,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774855098466,"responseId":"chatcmpl-a544bc90caac7a75"}}
